{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1797,"text":"So I want to talk a little bit about seeing the world"},{"time":4264,"text":"from a totally unique point of view,"},{"time":6990,"text":"and this world I'm going to talk about is the micro world."},{"time":10015,"text":"I've found, after doing this for many, many years,"},{"time":12595,"text":"that there's a magical world behind reality."},{"time":15311,"text":"And that can be seen directly through a microscope,"},{"time":18470,"text":"and I'm going to show you some of this today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":20575,"text":"So let's start off looking at something rather not-so-small,"},{"time":24262,"text":"something that we can see with our naked eye,"},{"time":26526,"text":"and that's a bee. So when you look at this bee,"},{"time":28967,"text":"it's about this size here, it's about a centimeter."},{"time":31863,"text":"But to really see the details of the bee, and really"},{"time":34151,"text":"appreciate what it is, you have to look a little bit closer."},{"time":37880,"text":"So that's just the eye of the bee with a microscope,"},{"time":40966,"text":"and now all of a sudden you can see that the bee has"},{"time":43313,"text":"thousands of individual eyes called ommatidia,"},{"time":46144,"text":"and they actually have sensory hairs in their eyes"},{"time":48576,"text":"so they know when they're right up close to something,"},{"time":50945,"text":"because they can't see in stereo."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54649,"text":"As we go smaller, here is a human hair."},{"time":58353,"text":"A human hair is about the smallest thing that the eye can see."},{"time":61172,"text":"It's about a tenth of a millimeter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63906,"text":"And as we go smaller again,"},{"time":65082,"text":"about ten times smaller than that, is a cell."},{"time":68488,"text":"So you could fit 10 human cells"},{"time":71071,"text":"across the diameter of a human hair."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74737,"text":"So when we would look at cells, this is how I really got"},{"time":76323,"text":"involved in biology and science is by looking"},{"time":79591,"text":"at living cells in the microscope."},{"time":82058,"text":"When I first saw living cells in a microscope, I was"},{"time":84129,"text":"absolutely enthralled and amazed at what they looked like."},{"time":88028,"text":"So if you look at the cell like that from the immune system,"},{"time":91344,"text":"they're actually moving all over the place."},{"time":93183,"text":"This cell is looking for foreign objects,"},{"time":96933,"text":"bacteria, things that it can find."},{"time":99290,"text":"And it's looking around, and when it finds something,"},{"time":101938,"text":"and recognizes it being foreign,"},{"time":104234,"text":"it will actually engulf it and eat it."},{"time":105526,"text":"So if you look right there, it finds that little bacterium,"},{"time":109810,"text":"and it engulfs it and eats it."},{"time":115432,"text":"If you take some heart cells from an animal,"},{"time":118613,"text":"and put it in a dish, they'll just sit there and beat."},{"time":121509,"text":"That's their job. Every cell has a mission in life,"},{"time":125099,"text":"and these cells, the mission is"},{"time":126900,"text":"to move blood around our body."},{"time":130427,"text":"These next cells are nerve cells, and right now,"},{"time":133211,"text":"as we see and understand what we're looking at,"},{"time":136147,"text":"our brains and our nerve cells are actually doing this"},{"time":138261,"text":"right now. They're not just static. They're moving around"},{"time":140803,"text":"making new connections, and that's what happens when we learn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144305,"text":"As you go farther down this scale here,"},{"time":147095,"text":"that's a micron, or a micrometer, and we go"},{"time":149999,"text":"all the way down to here to a nanometer"},{"time":152347,"text":"and an angstrom. Now, an angstrom is the size"},{"time":155104,"text":"of the diameter of a hydrogen atom."},{"time":158471,"text":"That's how small that is."},{"time":160104,"text":"And microscopes that we have today can actually see"},{"time":162421,"text":"individual atoms. So these are some pictures"},{"time":165479,"text":"of individual atoms. Each bump here is an individual atom."},{"time":168312,"text":"This is a ring of cobalt atoms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171141,"text":"So this whole world, the nano world, this area in here"},{"time":173799,"text":"is called the nano world, and the nano world,"},{"time":176994,"text":"the whole micro world that we see,"},{"time":180128,"text":"there's a nano world that is wrapped up within that, and"},{"time":183161,"text":"the whole -- and that is the world of molecules and atoms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187556,"text":"But I want to talk about this larger world,"},{"time":190014,"text":"the world of the micro world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192351,"text":"So if you were a little tiny bug living in a flower,"},{"time":196470,"text":"what would that flower look like, if the flower was this big?"},{"time":199621,"text":"It wouldn't look or feel like anything that we see"},{"time":202136,"text":"when we look at a flower. So if you look at this flower here,"},{"time":205430,"text":"and you're a little bug, if you're on that surface"},{"time":207262,"text":"of that flower, that's what the terrain would look like."},{"time":211328,"text":"The petal of that flower looks like that, so the ant"},{"time":213704,"text":"is kind of crawling over these objects, and if you look"},{"time":216385,"text":"a little bit closer at this stigma and the stamen here,"},{"time":219729,"text":"this is the style of that flower, and you notice"},{"time":222474,"text":"that it's got these little -- these are like little jelly-like things"},{"time":226699,"text":"that are what are called spurs. These are nectar spurs."},{"time":231441,"text":"So this little ant that's crawling here, it's like"},{"time":234058,"text":"it's in a little Willy Wonka land."},{"time":235884,"text":"It's like a little Disneyland for them. It's not like what we see."},{"time":240019,"text":"These are little bits of individual grain of pollen"},{"time":243922,"text":"there and there, and here is a --"},{"time":247368,"text":"what you see as one little yellow dot of pollen,"},{"time":249946,"text":"when you look in a microscope, it's actually made"},{"time":251910,"text":"of thousands of little grains of pollen."},{"time":255674,"text":"So this, for example, when you see bees flying around"},{"time":257909,"text":"these little plants, and they're collecting pollen,"},{"time":260714,"text":"those pollen grains that they're collecting, they pack"},{"time":263137,"text":"into their legs and they take it back to the hive,"},{"time":265570,"text":"and that's what makes the beehive,"},{"time":268200,"text":"the wax in the beehive. And they're also collecting nectar,"},{"time":272018,"text":"and that's what makes the honey that we eat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275929,"text":"Here's a close-up picture, or this is actually a regular picture"},{"time":279186,"text":"of a water hyacinth, and if you had really, really good vision,"},{"time":281859,"text":"with your naked eye, you'd see it about that well."},{"time":284420,"text":"There's the stamen and the pistil. But look what the stamen"},{"time":287048,"text":"and the pistil look like in a microscope. That's the stamen."},{"time":290562,"text":"So that's thousands of little grains of pollen there,"},{"time":293213,"text":"and there's the pistil there, and these are the little things"},{"time":296499,"text":"called trichomes. And that's what makes the flower give"},{"time":300218,"text":"a fragrance, and plants actually communicate"},{"time":304178,"text":"with one another through their fragrances."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309572,"text":"I want to talk about something really ordinary,"},{"time":311940,"text":"just ordinary sand."},{"time":313864,"text":"I became interested in sand about 10 years ago,"},{"time":315794,"text":"when I first saw sand from Maui,"},{"time":318355,"text":"and in fact, this is a little bit of sand from Maui."},{"time":321502,"text":"So sand is about a tenth of a millimeter in size."},{"time":324533,"text":"Each sand grain is about a tenth of a millimeter in size."},{"time":327444,"text":"But when you look closer at this, look at what's there."},{"time":330027,"text":"It's really quite amazing. You have microshells there."},{"time":333529,"text":"You have things like coral."},{"time":335722,"text":"You have fragments of other shells. You have olivine."},{"time":339256,"text":"You have bits of a volcano. There's a little bit"},{"time":341452,"text":"of a volcano there. You have tube worms."},{"time":344079,"text":"An amazing array of incredible things exist in sand."},{"time":348805,"text":"And the reason that is, is because in a place like this island,"},{"time":351484,"text":"a lot of the sand is made of biological material"},{"time":353850,"text":"because the reefs provide a place where all these"},{"time":356847,"text":"microscopic animals or macroscopic animals grow,"},{"time":360737,"text":"and when they die, their shells and their teeth"},{"time":363075,"text":"and their bones break up and they make grains of sand,"},{"time":365417,"text":"things like coral and so forth."},{"time":368387,"text":"So here's, for example, a picture of sand from Maui."},{"time":372180,"text":"This is from Lahaina,"},{"time":374717,"text":"and when we're walking along a beach, we're actually"},{"time":376447,"text":"walking along millions of years of biological and geological history."},{"time":379901,"text":"We don't realize it, but it's actually a record"},{"time":382368,"text":"of that entire ecology."},{"time":384941,"text":"So here we see, for example, a sponge spicule,"},{"time":388099,"text":"two bits of coral here,"},{"time":390685,"text":"that's a sea urchin spine. Really some amazing stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":394535,"text":"So when I first looked at this, I was -- I thought,"},{"time":396912,"text":"gee, this is like a little treasure trove here."},{"time":398661,"text":"I couldn't believe it, and I'd go around dissecting"},{"time":400827,"text":"the little bits out and making photographs of them."},{"time":404136,"text":"Here's what most of the sand in our world looks like."},{"time":406647,"text":"These are quartz crystals and feldspar,"},{"time":409908,"text":"so most sand in the world on the mainland"},{"time":412369,"text":"is made of quartz crystal and feldspar. It's the erosion of granite rock."},{"time":416119,"text":"So mountains are built up, and they erode away by water"},{"time":420470,"text":"and rain and ice and so forth,"},{"time":422497,"text":"and they become grains of sand."},{"time":423803,"text":"There's some sand that's really much more colorful."},{"time":426253,"text":"These are sand from near the Great Lakes,"},{"time":428337,"text":"and you can see that it's filled with minerals"},{"time":430348,"text":"like pink garnet and green epidote, all kinds of amazing stuff,"},{"time":433840,"text":"and if you look at different sands from different places,"},{"time":436224,"text":"every single beach, every single place you look at sand,"},{"time":439475,"text":"it's different. Here's from Big Sur, like they're little jewels."},{"time":444507,"text":"There are places in Africa where they do the mining"},{"time":446996,"text":"of jewels, and you go to the sand where the rivers have"},{"time":451165,"text":"the sand go down to the ocean, and it's like literally looking"},{"time":453464,"text":"at tiny jewels through the microscope."},{"time":456327,"text":"So every grain of sand is unique. Every beach is different."},{"time":459504,"text":"Every single grain is different. There are no two grains"},{"time":462686,"text":"of sand alike in the world."},{"time":464386,"text":"Every grain of sand is coming somewhere and going somewhere."},{"time":467918,"text":"They're like a snapshot in time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471646,"text":"Now sand is not only on Earth, but sand is"},{"time":475069,"text":"ubiquitous throughout the universe. In fact, outer space"},{"time":477667,"text":"is filled with sand, and that sand comes together"},{"time":481331,"text":"to make our planets and the Moon."},{"time":484528,"text":"And you can see those in micrometeorites."},{"time":486110,"text":"This is some micrometeorites that the Army gave me,"},{"time":488653,"text":"and they get these out of the drinking wells in the South Pole."},{"time":491747,"text":"And they're quite amazing-looking, and these are the"},{"time":494493,"text":"tiny constituents that make up the world that we live in --"},{"time":498917,"text":"the planets and the Moon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":500832,"text":"So NASA wanted me to take some pictures of Moon sand,"},{"time":504076,"text":"so they sent me sand from all the different landings"},{"time":506339,"text":"of the Apollo missions that happened 40 years ago."},{"time":510817,"text":"And I started taking pictures with my three-dimensional microscopes."},{"time":514457,"text":"This was the first picture I took. It was kind of amazing."},{"time":517424,"text":"I thought it looked kind of a little bit like the Moon, which is sort of interesting."},{"time":521207,"text":"Now, the way my microscopes work is, normally"},{"time":523870,"text":"in a microscope you can see very little at one time,"},{"time":526336,"text":"so what you have to do is you have to refocus the microscope,"},{"time":529283,"text":"keep taking pictures, and then I have a computer program"},{"time":533074,"text":"that puts all those pictures together"},{"time":535548,"text":"into one picture so you can see actually what it looks like,"},{"time":538670,"text":"and I do that in 3D. So there, you can see,"},{"time":541905,"text":"is a left-eye view. There's a right-eye view."},{"time":544607,"text":"So sort of left-eye view, right-eye view."}]},{"cues":[{"time":547160,"text":"Now something's interesting here. This looks very different"},{"time":549528,"text":"than any sand on Earth that I've ever seen, and I've"},{"time":551906,"text":"seen a lot of sand on Earth, believe me. (Laughter)"},{"time":555706,"text":"Look at this hole in the middle. That hole was caused"},{"time":558664,"text":"by a micrometeorite hitting the Moon."},{"time":561003,"text":"Now, the Moon has no atmosphere, so micrometeorites"},{"time":563360,"text":"come in continuously, and the whole surface of the Moon"},{"time":566576,"text":"is covered with powder now, because for four billion years"},{"time":569176,"text":"it's been bombarded by micrometeorites,"},{"time":571970,"text":"and when micrometeorites come in at about"},{"time":574360,"text":"20 to 60,000 miles an hour, they vaporize on contact."},{"time":578370,"text":"And you can see here that that is --"},{"time":580280,"text":"that's sort of vaporized, and that material is holding this"},{"time":582874,"text":"little clump of little sand grains together."},{"time":585420,"text":"This is a very small grain of sand, this whole thing."},{"time":587599,"text":"And that's called a ring agglutinate."},{"time":589759,"text":"And many of the grains of sand on the Moon look like that,"},{"time":593703,"text":"and you'd never find that on Earth."},{"time":597160,"text":"Most of the sand on the Moon,"},{"time":600413,"text":"especially -- and you know when you look at the Moon,"},{"time":602112,"text":"there's the dark areas and the light areas. The dark areas"},{"time":604472,"text":"are lava flows. They're basaltic lava flows,"},{"time":608613,"text":"and that's what this sand looks like, very similar"},{"time":611278,"text":"to the sand that you would see in Haleakala."},{"time":615041,"text":"Other sands, when these micrometeorites come in,"},{"time":618464,"text":"they vaporize and they make these fountains,"},{"time":621553,"text":"these microscopic fountains that go up into the --"},{"time":624176,"text":"I was going to say \"up into the air,\" but there is no air --"},{"time":626540,"text":"goes sort of up, and these microscopic glass beads"},{"time":630791,"text":"are formed instantly, and they harden, and by the time"},{"time":633304,"text":"they fall down back to the surface of the Moon,"},{"time":636689,"text":"they have these beautiful colored glass spherules."},{"time":639585,"text":"And these are actually microscopic;"},{"time":641130,"text":"you need a microscope to see these."}]},{"cues":[{"time":644098,"text":"Now here's a grain of sand that is from the Moon,"},{"time":647535,"text":"and you can see that the entire"},{"time":649689,"text":"crystal structure is still there."},{"time":652172,"text":"This grain of sand is probably about"},{"time":654320,"text":"three and a half or four billion years old,"},{"time":656602,"text":"and it's never eroded away like the way we have sand"},{"time":658793,"text":"on Earth erodes away because of water and tumbling,"},{"time":662812,"text":"air, and so forth. All you can see is a little bit of erosion"},{"time":666062,"text":"down here by the Sun, has these solar storms,"},{"time":670669,"text":"and that's erosion by solar radiation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":675432,"text":"So what I've been trying to tell you today is"},{"time":678018,"text":"things even as ordinary as a grain of sand"},{"time":681587,"text":"can be truly extraordinary if you look closely"},{"time":684562,"text":"and if you look from a different and a new point of view."},{"time":687867,"text":"I think that this was best put by William Blake when he said,"},{"time":692242,"text":"\"To see a world in a grain of sand"},{"time":694784,"text":"and a heaven in a wild flower,"},{"time":697538,"text":"hold infinity in the palm of your hand,"},{"time":699871,"text":"and eternity in an hour.\""},{"time":702204,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}